ULCER-STOP,SIDE EFFECTS,الآثار الجانبية,"Gastrointestinal: The most frequent gastrointestinal adverse events include diarrhea and abdominal pain. The incidence of diarrhea can be minimized by administering after meals and at bedtime, and by avoiding coadministration of ULCER-STOP with magnesium-containing antacids.",
ULCER-STOP,DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION,الجرعة وطريقة الاستعمال,"The recommended adult oral dose of ULCER-STOP (misoprostol) for reducing the risk of NSAID-induced gastric ulcers is 200 mcg four times daily with food. If this dose cannot be tolerated, a dose of 100 mcg can be used. ULCER- STOP (misoprostol) should be taken for the duration of NSAID",
ULCER-STOP,OVERDOSAGE,فرط الجرعة,"Clinical signs that may indicate an overdose are sedation, tremor, convulsions, dyspnea, abdominal pain, diarrhea, fever, palpitations, hypotension, or bradycardia. Symptoms should be treated with supportive therapy.",
ORLISTAT HAMA PHARMA,SIDE EFFECTS,الآثار الجانبية,"Common with an incidence of ≥ 5%: Oily Spotting, Flatus with Discharge, Fatty/Oily Stool, Fecal Urgency, Oily Evacuation, Increased Defecation, Fecal Incontinence. GI adverse events may occur in some individuals over a period of 6 months or longer",
